obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (29866)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925&sectionId=29866&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Hindu Adoptions and Maintenance`
  line `Act, 1956.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-10- 2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (29867)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Application of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925&sectionId=29867&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act applies--`
  line
  line `(a) to any person, who is a Hindu by religion in any of its forms or developments, including a`
  line `Virashaiva, a Lingayat or a follower of the Brahmo, Prarthana or Arya Samaj,`
  line
  line `(b) to any person who is a Buddhist, Jaina or Sikh by religion, and`
  line
  line `(c) to any other person who is not a Muslim, Christian, Parsi or Jew by religion, unless it is`
  line `proved that any such person would not have been governed by the Hindu law or by any custom or`
  line `usage as part of that law in respect of any of the matters dealt with herein if this Act had not been`
  line passed.
  line
  line `Explanation.--The following persons are Hindus, Buddhists, Jainas or Sikhs by religion, as the case`
  line `may be:--`
  line
  line `(a) any child, legitimate or illegitimate, both of whose parents are Hindus, Buddhists, Jainas or`
  line `Sikhs by religion;`
  line
  line `(b) any child, legitimate or illegitimate, one of whose parents is a Hindu, Buddhist, Jaina or Sikh`
  line `by religion and who is brought up as a member of the tribe, community, group or family to which`
  line `such parent belongs or belonged; ^1`
  line `* * *`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(bb) any child, legitimate or illegitimate, who has been abandoned both by his father and mother`
  line `or whose parentage is not known and who in either case is brought up as a Hindu, Buddhist, Jaina or`
  line `Sikh; and]`
  line
  line `(c) any person who is a convert or re-convert to the Hindu, Buddhist, Jaina or Sikh religion.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), nothing contained in this Act shall apply`
  line `to the members of any Scheduled Tribe within the meaning of clause (25) of article 366 of the`
  line `Constitution unless the Central Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, otherwise directs.`
  line
  line `(3) The expression "Hindu" in any portion of this Act shall be construed as if it included a person`
  line `who, though not a Hindu by religion, is, nevertheless, a person to whom this Act applies by virtue of the`
  line `provisions contained in this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word and omitted by Act 45 of 1962, s. 2 (w.e.f. 19-11-1962).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 19-11-1962).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (29868)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925&sectionId=29868&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,―`
  line
  line `(a) the expressions "custom" and "usage" signify any rule which, having been continuously and`
  line `uniformly observed for a long time, has obtained the force of law among Hindus in any local area,`
  line `tribe, community, group or family:`
  line
  line `Provided that the rule is certain and not unreasonable or opposed to public policy: and`
  line
  line `Provided further that, in the case of a rule applicable only to a family, it has not been discontinued`
  line `by the family;`
  line
  line `(b) "maintenance" includes―`
  line
  line `(i) in all cases, provision for food, clothing, residence, education and medical attendance and`
  line treatment;
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of an unmarried daughter, also the reasonable expenses of and incident to her`
  line marriage;
  line
  line `(c) "minor" means a person who has not completed his or her age of eighteen years.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (29869)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Overriding effect of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925&sectionId=29869&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise expressly provided in this Act,―`
  line
  line `(a) any text, rule or interpretation of Hindu law or any custom or usage as part of that law in force`
  line `immediately before the commencement of this Act shall cease to have effect with respect to any`
  line `matter for which provision is made in this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) any other law in force immediately before the commencement of this Act shall cease to apply`
  line `to Hindus in so far as it is inconsistent with any of the provisions contained in this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (29870)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Adoptions to be regulated by this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925&sectionId=29870&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) No adoption shall be made after the`
  line `commencement of this Act by or to a Hindu except in accordance with the provisions contained in this`
  line `Chapter, and any adoption made in contravention of the said provisions shall be void.`
  line
  line `(2) An adoption which is void shall neither create any rights in the adoptive family in favour of any`
  line `person which he or she could not have acquired except by reason of the adoption, nor destroy the rights of`
  line `any person in the family of his or her birth.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (29871)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Requisites of a valid adoption.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925&sectionId=29871&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `No adoption shall be valid unless--`
  line
  line `(i) the person adopting has the capacity, and also the right, to take in adoption;`
  line
  line `(ii) the person giving in adoption has the capacity to do so;`
  line
  line `(iii) the person adopted is capable of being taken in adoption; and`
  line
  line `(iv) the adoption is made in compliance with the other conditions mentioned in this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (29872)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Capacity of a male Hindu to take in adoption.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925&sectionId=29872&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Any male Hindu who is of sound mind and is`
  line `not a minor has the capacity to takes on or a daughter in adoption:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if he has a wife living, he shall not adopt except with the consent of his wife unless the`
  line `wife has completely and finally renounced the word or has ceased to be a Hindu or has been declared by a`
  line `court of competent jurisdiction to be of unsound mind.`
  line
  line `Explanation.―If a person has more than one wife living at the time of adoption, the consent of all the`
  line `wives is necessary unless the consent of any one of them is unnecessary for any of the reasons specified`
  line `in the preceding proviso.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (29873)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Capacity of a female Hindu to take in adoption.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 30 of 2010, s. 3, for section 8 (w.e.f. 31-8-2010).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925&sectionId=29873&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `^1[8. Capacity of a female Hindu to take in adoption.―Any female Hindu who is of sound mind`
  line `and is not a minor has the capacity to take a son or daughter in adoption:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if she has a husband living, she shall not adopt a son or daughter except with the`
  line `consent of her husband unless the husband has completely and finally renounced the world or has ceased`
  line `to be a Hindu or has been declared by a court of competent jurisdiction to be of unsound mind.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (29874)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Persons capable of giving in adoption.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925&sectionId=29874&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person except the father or mother or the`
  line `guardian of a child shall have the capacity to give the child in adoption.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (4), the father or the mother, if alive, shall have equal`
  line `right to give a son or daughter in adoption:`
  line
  line `Provided that such right shall not be exercised by either of them save with the consent of the other`
  line `unless one of them has completely and finally renounced the world or has ceased to be a Hindu or has`
  line `been declared by a court of competent jurisdiction to be of unsound mind.]`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `^3[(4) Where both the father and mother are dead or have completely and finally renounced the world`
  line `or have abandoned the child or have been declared by a court of competent jurisdiction to be of unsound`
  line `mind or where the parentage of the child is not known, the guardian of the child may give the child in`
  line `adoption with the previous permission of the court to any person including the guardian himself.]`
  line
  line `(5) Before granting permission to a guardian under sub-section (4), the court shall be satisfied that the`
  line `adoption will be for the welfare of the child, due consideration being for this purpose given to the wishes`
  line `of the child having regard to the age and understanding of the child and that the applicant for permission`
  line `has not received or agreed to receive and that no person has made or given or agreed to make or give to`
  line `the applicant any payment or reward in consideration of the adoption except such as the court may`
  line sanction.
  line
  line `Explanation.For the purposes of this section`
  line
  line `(i) the expressions father and mother do not include an adoptive father and an adoptive`
  line `mother; ^4* * *`
  line
  line `^5[(ia) guardian means a person having the care of the person of a child or of both his person and`
  line `property and includes`
  line
  line `(a) a guardian appointed by the will of the child's father or mother, and`
  line
  line `(b) a guardian appointed or declared by a court; and]`
  line
  line `(ii) court means the city civil court or a district court within the local limits of whose`
  line `jurisdiction the child to be adopted ordinarily resides.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 31-8-2010).`
  line
  line `2. Sub-section (3) omitted by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 31-8-2010).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 45 of 1962, s. 3, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 29-11-1962).`
  line
  line `4. The word and omitted by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 29-11-1962).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by s. 3, ibid.(w.e.f. 29-11-1962).`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (29875)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Persons who may be adopted.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925&sectionId=29875&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `No person shall be capable of being taken in adoption unless the`
  line `following conditions are fulfilled, namely:―`
  line
  line `(i) he or she is a Hindu;`
  line
  line `(ii) he or she has not already been adopted;`
  line
  line `(iii) he or she has not been married, unless there is a custom or usage applicable to the parties`
  line `which permits persons who are married being taken in adoption;`
  line
  line `(iv) he or she has not completed the age of fifteen years, unless there is a custom or usage`
  line `applicable to the parties which permits persons who have completed the age of fifteen years being`
  line `taken in adoption.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (29876)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Other conditions for a valid adoption.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 45 of 1962, s. 4 (w.e.f. 29-11-1962).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925&sectionId=29876&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `In every adoption, the following conditions must be`
  line `complied with:―`
  line
  line `(i) if the adoption is of a son, the adoptive father or mother by whom the adoption is made must`
  line `not have a Hindu son sons son or sons sons son (whether by legitimate blood relationship or by`
  line `adoption) living at the time of adoption;`
  line
  line `(ii) if the adoption is of a daughter, the adoptive father or mother by whom the adoption is made`
  line `must not have a Hindu daughter or sons daughter (whether by legitimate blood relationship or by`
  line `adoption) living at the time of adoption;`
  line
  line `(iii) if the adoption is by a male and the person to be adopted is a female, the adoptive father is at`
  line `least twenty-one years older than the person to be adopted;`
  line
  line `(iv) if the adoption is by a female and the person to be adopted is a male, the adoptive mother is at`
  line `least twenty-one years older than the person to be adopted;`
  line
  line `(v) the same child may not be adopted simultaneously by two or more persons;`
  line
  line `(vi) the child to be adopted must be actually given and taken in adoption by the parents or`
  line `guardian concerned or under their authority with intent to transfer the child from the family of its`
  line `birth ^1[or in the case of an abandoned child or a child whose parentage is not known, from the place`
  line `or family where it has been brought up] to the family of its adoption:`
  line
  line `Provided that the performance of datta homam shall not be essential to the validity of an adoption.`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (29877)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Effects of adoption.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925&sectionId=29877&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `An adopted child shall be deemed to be the child of his or her adoptive`
  line `father or mother for all purposes with effect from the date of the adoption and from such date all the ties`
  line `of the child in the family of his or her birth shall be deemed to be severed and replaced by those created`
  line `by the adoption in the adoptive family:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) the child cannot marry any person whom he or she could not have married if he or she had`
  line `continued in the family of his or her birth;`
  line
  line `(b) any property which vested in the adopted child before the adoption shall continue to vest in`
  line `such person subject to the obligations, if any, attaching to the ownership of such property, including`
  line `the obligation to maintain relatives in the family of his or her birth;`
  line
  line `(c) the adopted child shall not divest any person of any estate which vested in him or her before`
  line `the adoption.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (29878)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Right of adoptive parents to dispose of their properties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925&sectionId=29878&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Subject to any agreement to the`
  line `contrary, an adoption does not deprive the adoptive father or mother of the power to dispose of his or her`
  line `property by transfer inter vivos or by will.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (29879)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Determination of adoptive mother in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925&sectionId=29879&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1)Where a Hindu who has a wife living`
  line `adopts a child, she shall be deemed to be the adoptive mother.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an adoption has been made with the consent of more than one wife, the seniormost in`
  line `marriage among them shall be deemed to be the adoptive mother and the others to be step-mothers.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a widower or a bachelor adopts a child, any wife whom he subsequently marries shall be`
  line `deemed to be the step-mother of the adopted child.`
  line
  line `(4) Where a window or an unmarried woman adopts a child, any husband whom she marries`
  line `subsequently shall be deemed to be the step-father of the adopted child.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (29880)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Valid adoption not to be cancelled.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925&sectionId=29880&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `No adoption which has been validly made can be cancelled`
  line `by the adoptive father or mother or any other person, nor can the adopted child renounce his or her status`
  line `as such and return to the family of his or her birth.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (29881)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Presumption as to registered documents relating to adoptions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925&sectionId=29881&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any document`
  line `registered under any law for the time being in force is produced before any court purporting to record an`
  line `adoption made and is signed by the person giving and the person taking the child in adoption, the court`
  line `shall presume that the adoption has been made in compliance with the provisions of this Act unless and`
  line `until it is disproved.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh.--`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 16 of Act 78 of 1956.--In the Hindu Adaptation and Maintenance Act, 1956,`
  line `section 16 shall be re-numbered as sub-section (1) thereof, and after sub-section (1) as so re-numbered the`
  line `following sub-section shall be inserted namely:--`
  line
  line `"(2) In case any adoption made on or after the first day of January, 1977 no Court in Uttar Pradesh`
  line `shall accept any evidence in proof of the giving and taking of the child in adoption, except a document`
  line `recording an adoption, made and signed by the person giving and the person taking the child in adoption,`
  line `and registered under any law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `Provided that secondary evidence of such document shall be admissible in the circumstances and the`
  line `manner laid down in the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872).".`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 57 of 1976, s. 35]`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (29882)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Prohibition of certain payments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925&sectionId=29882&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall receive or agree to receive any payment`
  line `or other reward in consideration of the adoption of any person, and no person shall make or give or agree`
  line `to make or give to any other person any payment or reward the receipt of which is prohibited by this`
  line section.
  line
  line `(2) If any person contravenes the provisions of sub-section(1), he shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment which may extend to six months, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) No prosecution under this section shall be instituted without the previous sanction of the State`
  line `Government or an officer authorised by the State Government in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (29883)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Maintenance of wife.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. Clause (c) omitted by Act 6 of 2019, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-3-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925&sectionId=29883&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this section, a Hindu wife, whether`
  line `married before or after the commencement of this Act, shall be entitled to be maintained by her husband`
  line `during her life time.`
  line
  line `(2) A Hindu wife shall be entitled to live separately from her husband without forfeiting her claim to`
  line maintenance,
  line
  line `(a) if he is guilty of desertion, that is to say, of abandoning her without reasonable cause and`
  line `without her consent or against her wish, or of wilfully neglecting her;`
  line
  line `(b) if he has treated her with such cruelty as to cause a reasonable apprehension in her mind that it`
  line `will be harmful or injurious to live with her husband;`
  line
  line ^1*****
  line
  line `(d) if he has any other wife living;`
  line
  line `(e) if he keeps a concubine in the same house in which his wife is living or habitually resides with`
  line `a concubine elsewhere;`
  line
  line `(f) if he has ceased to be a Hindu by conversion to another religion;`
  line
  line `(g) if there is any other cause justifying her living separately.`
  line
  line `(3) A Hindu wife shall not be entitled to separate residence and maintenance from her husband if she`
  line `is unchaste or ceases to be a Hindu by conversion to another religion.`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (29884)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Maintenance of widowed daughter-in-law.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925&sectionId=29884&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Hindu wife, whether married before or after`
  line `the commencement of this Act, shall be entitled to be maintained after the death of her husband by her`
  line `father-in-law:`
  line
  line `Provided and to the extent that she is unable to maintain herself out of her own earnings or other`
  line `property or, where she has no property of her own, is unable to obtain maintenance―`
  line
  line `(a) from the estate of her husband or her father or mother, or`
  line
  line `(b) from her son or daughter, if any, or his or her estate.`
  line
  line `(2) Any obligation under sub-section (1) shall not be enforceable if the father-in-law has not the`
  line `means to do so from any coparcenary property in his possession out of which the daughter-in- law has not`
  line `obtained any share, and any such obligation shall cease on the remarriage of the daughter-in-law.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (29885)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Maintenance of children and aged parents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925&sectionId=29885&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this section a`
  line `Hindu is bound, during his or her life-time, to maintain his or her legitimate or illegitimate children and`
  line `his or her aged or infirm parents.`
  line
  line `(2) A legitimate or illegitimate child may claim maintenance from his or her father or mother so long`
  line `as the child is a minor.`
  line
  line `(3) The obligation of a person to maintain his or her aged or infirm parent or a daughter who is`
  line `unmarried extends in so far as the parent or the unmarried daughter, as the case may be, is unable to`
  line `maintain himself or herself out of his or her own earnings or other property.`
  line
  line `Explanation.―In this section "parent" includes a childless step-mother.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (29886)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Dependants defined.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925&sectionId=29886&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of this Chapter "dependants" mean the following`
  line `relatives of the deceased:--`
  line
  line `(i) his or her father;`
  line
  line `(ii) his or her mother;`
  line
  line `(iii) his widow, so long as she does not re-marry;`
  line
  line `(iv) his or her son or the son of his predeceased son or the son of a predeceased son of his`
  line `pre-deceased son, so long as he is a minor: provided and to the extent that he is unable to obtain`
  line `maintenance, in the case of a grandson from his fathers or mothers estate, and in the case of a`
  line `great-grandson, from the estate of his father or mother or fathers father or fathers mother;--`
  line
  line `(v) his or her unmarried daughter, or the unmarried daughter of his predeceased son or the`
  line `unmarried daughter of a predeceased son of his predeceased son, so long as she remains unmarried:`
  line
  line `provided and to the extent that she is unable to obtain maintenance, in the case of a grand-daughter`
  line `from her fathers or mothers estate and in the case of a great-grand-daughter from the estate of her`
  line `father or mother or father's father or fathers mother;`
  line
  line `(vi) his widowed daughter: provided and to the extent that she is unable to obtain maintenance--`
  line
  line `(a) from the estate of her husband; or`
  line
  line `(b) from her son or daughter if any, or his or her estate; or`
  line
  line `(c) from her father-in-law or his father or the estate of either of them;`
  line
  line `(vii) any widow of his son or of a son of his predeceased son, so long as she does not re-marry:`
  line
  line `provided and to the extent that she is unable to obtain maintenance from her husbands estate, or from`
  line `her son or daughter, if any, or his or her estate; or in the case of a grandsons widow, also from her`
  line `father-in-laws estate;`
  line
  line `(viii) his or her minor illegitimate son, so long as he remains a minor;`
  line
  line `(ix) his or her illegitimate daughter, so long as she remains unmarried.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (29887)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Maintenance of dependants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925&sectionId=29887&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), the heirs of a`
  line `deceased Hindu are bound to maintain the dependants of the deceased out of the estate inherited by them`
  line `from the deceased.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a dependant has not obtained, by testamentary or intestate succession, any share in the`
  line `estate of a Hindu dying after the commencement of this Act, the dependant shall be entitled, subject to the`
  line `provisions of this Act, to maintenance from those who take the estate.`
  line
  line `(3) The liability of each of the persons who takes the estate shall be in proportion to the value of the`
  line `share or part of the estate taken by him or her.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2) or sub-section (3), no person who is`
  line `himself or herself a dependant shall be liable to contribute to the maintenance of others, if he or she has`
  line `obtained a share or part the value of which is, or would, if the liability to contribute were enforced,`
  line `become less than what would be awarded to him or her by way of maintenance under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (29888)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Amount of maintenance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925&sectionId=29888&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be in the discretion of the court to determine whether any,`
  line `and if so what, maintenance shall be awarded under the provisions of this Act, and in doing so the court`
  line `shall have due regard to the considerations set out in sub-section (2) or sub-section (3), as the case may`
  line `be, so far as they are applicable.`
  line
  line `(2) In determining the amount of maintenance, if any, to be awarded to a wife, children or aged on`
  line `infirm parents under this Act, regard shall be had to--`
  line
  line `(a) the position and status of the parties;`
  line
  line `(b) the reasonable wants of the claimant;`
  line
  line `(c) if the claimant is living separately, whether the claimant is justified in doing so;`
  line
  line `(d) the value of the claimants property and any income derived from such property, or from the`
  line `claimant's own earnings or from any other source;`
  line
  line `(e) the number of persons entitled to maintenance under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) In determining the amount of maintenance, if any, to be awarded to a dependent under this Act,`
  line `regard shall be had to--`
  line
  line `(a) the net value of the estate of the deceased after providing for the payment of his debts;`
  line
  line `(b) the provision, if any, made under a will of the deceased in respect of the dependant;`
  line
  line `(c) the degree of relationship between the two;`
  line
  line `(d) the reasonable wants of the dependant;`
  line
  line `(e) the past relations between the dependant and the deceased;`
  line
  line `(f) the value of the property of the dependant and any income derived from such property; or from`
  line `his or her earnings or from any other source;`
  line
  line `(g) the number of dependants entitled to maintenance under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (29889)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Claimant to maintenance should be a Hindu.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925&sectionId=29889&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `No person shall be entitled to claim`
  line `maintenance under this Chapter if he or she has ceased to be a Hindu by conversion to another religion.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (29890)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Amount of maintenance may be altered on change of circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925&sectionId=29890&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `The amount of`
  line `maintenance, whether fixed by a decree of court or by agreement, either before or after the commencement of this Act, may be altered subsequently if there is a material change in the circumstances`
  line `justifying such alteration.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (29891)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Debts to have priority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925&sectionId=29891&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions contained in section 27 debts of every`
  line `description contracted or payable by the deceased shall have priority over the claims of his dependants for`
  line `maintenance under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (29892)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Maintenance when to be a charge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925&sectionId=29892&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `A dependant’s claim for maintenance under this Act shall`
  line `not be a charge on the estate of the deceased or any portion thereof, unless one has been created by the`
  line `will of the deceased, by a decree of court, by agreement between the dependant and the owner of the`
  line `estate or portion, or otherwise.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (29893)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Effect of transfer of property on right to maintenance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925&sectionId=29893&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Where a dependant has a right to receive`
  line `maintenance out of an estate and such estate or any part thereof is transferred, the right to receive`
  line `maintenance may be enforced against the transferee if the transferee has notice of the right, or if the`
  line `transfer is gratuitous; but not against the transferee for consideration and without notice of the right.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (29894)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title Repealed.
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925&sectionId=29894&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `[Repeals.]Rep. by the Repealing and`
  line `Amending Act, 1960 (58 of1960), s. 2`
  line `and the First Schedule (w.e.f. 26-11-1960).`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (29895)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title Savings
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925&sectionId=29895&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00015_195678_1517807320925
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in this Act shall affect any adoption made before the`
  line `commencement of this Act, and the validity and effect of any such adoption shall be determined as if this`
  line `Act had not been passed.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
